title: Salsa Verde Carnitas
summary: Salsa Verde Carnitas might be a good recipe to expand your hor d'oeuvre recipe box. One serving contains 678 calories, 60g of protein, and 29g of fat. For $3.57 per serving, this recipe covers 44% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe serves 6. Plenty of people really liked this Mexican dish. Head to the store and pick up seasoned rice vinegar, onion, cumin seeds, and a few other things to make it today. This recipe from Simply Recipes has 326 fans. It is a good option if you're following a gluten free diet. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 3 hours and 30 minutes. Overall, this recipe earns an awesome spoonacular score of 96%. Salsa Verde Carnitas, No-Waste Tacos de Carnitas with Salsa Verde, and Carnitas and Avocado-Plantain Rice with Tomatillo Salsa Verde + 15% off @FluentCity are very similar to this recipe.

winePairing.pairingText: Dipping Sauce works really well with Sparkling rosé and Sparkling Wine. If you're serving a selection of appetizers, you can't go wrong with these. Both are very food friendly and complement a variety of flavors. The Bellissima Sparkling rosé with a 4.5 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 24 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Bellissima Sparkling Rose
productMatches.description: This is an elegant, bright rosé, with hints of strawberry and grapefruit, and a soft, persistent foam. Uncorked at the very last minute, Bellissima Sparkling Rosé pairs perfectly with smoked salmon, shellfish, and seafood hor d’oeuvres such as tuna tartare, sushi, and sashimi.
